team19.weatherapp

Class LongTermForecast

  • java.lang.Object
    • team19.weatherapp.LongTermForecast

  • public class LongTermForecast
extends java.lang.Object
    The LongTermForecast class holds all of the long term weather data for the specified city. When the json is parsed, it is passed into the LongTermForecast constructor, which retrieves the data from the JSONObject and saves it into multiple variables. Once saved, a user can easy access any of these variables by referencing them through the city object.
    Author:
    Scott Mackie

      • LongTermForecast

        public LongTermForecast(org.json.JSONObject j,
                        char tempUnits)
        The LongTermForecast constructor retrieves the JSONObject data, and saves the data into variable fields. The data is saved in the format specified by tempUnits and windUnits.
        Parameters:
        j - This is the JSONObject that the city data is retrieved from
        tempUnits - The temperature units shows which units the temperature data should be stored in
